text: I’m Afrikaans. I’m African. And I’m done pretending our future lies anywhere but here. If we want to protect our language, our culture, and our dignity — it has to be through unity with Africa, not distance from it. Afrikaans doesn’t survive by isolating — it survives by standing proudly, shoulder to shoulder, with every African building a new future. This is where we belong. This is where we fight to stay. #politicssouthafrica #southafricapolitics #politicalcommentary #politicsafrica #africa #panafricanism #afrikaners #africanunity #pieterkriel

They taught us to kneel before they taught us to speak. We were colonised not just with guns — but with Bibles. Today, we call it faith. We call it culture. But when religion writes our laws, opens our Parliament, and defines our morality, it’s not faith anymore — it’s mental captivity. You can believe what you want. But don’t confuse comfort with truth. And don’t call it freedom if you’re still obeying your master’s god. #politicssouthafrica #southafricapolitics #politicalcommentary #politicalanalysis #deconstruction #decolonisation #pieterkriel #africapolitics

South Africa’s so-called “unity government” isn’t about unity — it’s about profit. The ANC has abandoned its last moral standing by partnering with the DA, a party that’s done nothing for the poor in the Western Cape. While we argue over land and refugees, Ramaphosa flies to Washington to sell South Africa to foreign investors. This isn’t transformation — it’s betrayal. #politicssouthafrica #southafricapolitics #politicalcommentary #politicalanalysis #pieterkriel #democraticalliance #africannationalcongress

This isn’t about left or right. It’s about the fact that most white South Africans — especially in the Afrikaans community, were never taught the truth.

They were taught to feel innocent, not to be informed.

They don’t know what really happened under segregation. They don’t know about forced removals, land dispossession, Bantu Education, or the full machinery of apartheid because the system made sure they didn’t.

This ignorance isn’t accidental. It was engineered. #politicssouthafrica #southafricapolitics #politicalanalysis #politicalcommentary #pieterkriel #afrikaners #deconstruction #decolonisation
